231
00:14:02,408 --> 00:14:05,511
I feel like I'm part of a big project.

232
00:14:06,111 --> 00:14:08,247
It feels as though

233
00:14:08,547 --> 00:14:11,217
I'm dealing with a large amount of money.

234
00:14:11,317 --> 00:14:14,086
Even from a financial point of view,

235
00:14:14,153 --> 00:14:18,023
I feel like we're placed in charge of
something very big.

236
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:20,960
I'm saying this in a very broad sense.

237
00:14:22,828 --> 00:14:26,465
<i>Eight in the evening. All the teams have
brought in their equipment.</i>

238
00:14:26,732 --> 00:14:28,667
<i>It's finally time to begin preparation.</i>

239
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:30,803
SPECIAL EFFECTS

240
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:34,206
<i>Yabe is connecting equipment for
special effects</i>

241
00:14:34,273 --> 00:14:37,443
<i>onto the large structure that will
hang over the center of the arena.</i>

242
00:14:38,777 --> 00:14:41,413
Ms. Nikami, can I tape up
all the connectors?

243
00:14:42,982 --> 00:14:44,917
No, not yet. I'll attach it

244
00:14:44,984 --> 00:14:46,118
over here first.

245
00:14:46,518 --> 00:14:49,088
{\an8}<i>It's my very first arena tour.</i>

246
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:52,791
{\an8}<i>I've always wanted to be part of
a tour group,</i>

247
00:14:52,858 --> 00:14:55,160
{\an8}so I'm filled with nerves and anxiety.

248
00:14:55,628 --> 00:14:59,865
I want to do all that I can
and give my very best.

249
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:04,770
<i>It's only the first day, but there
is no end to the workload.</i>

250
00:15:06,105 --> 00:15:07,706
<i>Until the tour ends,</i>

251
00:15:07,773 --> 00:15:10,976
<i>they can neither get much sleep
nor take any time off.</i>

252
00:15:13,512 --> 00:15:17,249
<i>But they are happy to be
involved in this work.</i>

253
00:15:21,720 --> 00:15:23,522
This is baby powder.

254
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:26,725
Static electricity makes
the confetti stick together.

255
00:15:26,926 --> 00:15:28,894
This is to prevent that from happening.

256
00:15:30,029 --> 00:15:33,999
<i>This is the secret to prevent the shiny
confetti from sticking together.</i>

257
00:15:35,868 --> 00:15:37,703
This opening is too small.

258
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:40,239
My arms won't fit.

259
00:15:41,240 --> 00:15:44,076
<i>Drawn to the world that creates
these techniques,</i>

260
00:15:44,143 --> 00:15:46,178
<i>she chose this career for herself.</i>

261
00:15:47,846 --> 00:15:49,014
These are scrollers.

262
00:15:49,081 --> 00:15:55,754
They're devices that hang up above
and scatter gold and silver confetti.

263
00:15:59,658 --> 00:16:01,860
<i>But soon after,</i>

264
00:16:02,828 --> 00:16:07,866
<i>unexpected trouble befalls
Yabe and the special effects team.</i>

265
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:14,840
Don't block this side right here.

266
00:16:14,907 --> 00:16:16,241
It will block people out.

267
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:18,744
<i>The special mechanics team
operates the moving stage,</i>

268
00:16:18,811 --> 00:16:23,649
<i>which is necessary to create
a dynamic stage performance.</i>

269
00:16:24,616 --> 00:16:26,585
{\an8}<i>Fukuda, the youngest team member,</i>

270
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:31,023
{\an8}<i>is busy carrying and assembling
heavy steel frames.</i>

271
00:16:31,090 --> 00:16:32,791
{\an8}SPECIAL MECHANICS
FUKUDA SHOICHIRO (AGE 24)

272
00:16:32,858 --> 00:16:34,994
{\an8}Let's place this over there.

273
00:16:35,394 --> 00:16:37,663
My rank within this team is low,

274
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:41,166
but since I'm working with
all sorts of people,

275
00:16:41,233 --> 00:16:43,736
I want to make sure to inform them

276
00:16:44,303 --> 00:16:49,475
about things I have to do,
or things I know how to do,

277
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:51,777
and make sure I don't slow down the team.

278
00:16:52,111 --> 00:16:55,314
That's my goal this time around.

279
00:16:56,215 --> 00:16:57,216
{\an8}<i>At the same time,</i>

280
00:16:57,282 --> 00:17:01,487
{\an8}<i>Kuramochi is conducting
a meeting with the sound team.</i>

281
00:17:01,553 --> 00:17:05,457
{\an8}<i>They are discussing how to pass
the microphones during the concert.</i>

282
00:17:06,992 --> 00:17:09,895
When the performance ends,
go to the GL stairs

283
00:17:09,962 --> 00:17:13,999
and these four members will come

284
00:17:14,066 --> 00:17:16,135
to retrieve the handheld microphones.

285
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:18,704
As for who will retrieve them...

286
00:17:18,771 --> 00:17:22,040
<i>He explains the microphone schedule
for the entire two-hour concert</i>

287
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:24,109
<i>one performance at a time.</i>

288
00:17:25,077 --> 00:17:28,213
<i>It's hard to do everything perfectly.</i>

289
00:17:28,280 --> 00:17:31,216
<i>But because they strive for perfection,</i>

290
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:34,420
<i>even the smallest of details
do not go unnoticed.</i>

291
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,321
<i>But even then...</i>

292
00:17:38,157 --> 00:17:40,993
During the encore,
we'll take the microphones

293
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,395
and go toward the main stage.

294
00:17:43,829 --> 00:17:46,465
-And also remove the headsets?
-Yes, that's right.

295
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:50,536
<i>He receives a reminder
from an experienced member.</i>

296
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,006
<i>This is his first experience
as a stage chief.</i>

297
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:56,675
<i>It's a heavy responsibility.</i>

298
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:04,683
Ever since I started this job,
I've been preparing myself for this,

299
00:18:05,617 --> 00:18:08,187
so instead of panicking,

300
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:11,123
I feel like this is
a great challenging opportunity.

301
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:16,495
<i>And then, at 9:30 p.m...</i>

302
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:19,031
<i>trouble arises.</i>

303
00:18:19,698 --> 00:18:21,934
<i>An apparatus called the rounded truss,</i>

304
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,204
<i>used for attaching lights
and special effects,</i>

305
00:18:25,270 --> 00:18:27,072
<i>will not go up.</i>

306
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:29,641
{\an8}It might be the weight.

307
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,410
{\an8}STAGE FACILITATOR
MASAHIRO UEDA (AGE 27)

308
00:18:31,477 --> 00:18:34,713
{\an8}The calculation should be correct, but...

309
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:36,748
{\an8}it's overweight and won't go up.

310
00:18:37,783 --> 00:18:40,285
-We're taking two units down.
-Two units?

311
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:41,954
SPECIAL EFFECTS

312
00:18:42,020 --> 00:18:44,423
<i>Are some pieces of equipment
over the weight limit?</i>

313
00:18:45,090 --> 00:18:47,059
<i>They decide to test it out</i>

314
00:18:47,159 --> 00:18:52,331
<i>by dismantling the heaviest equipment
which happens to be the scroller.</i>

315
00:18:52,397 --> 00:18:54,333
<i>Yabe and her team are called.</i>

316
00:18:57,836 --> 00:18:58,871
-Hey.
-Yes.

317
00:18:59,204 --> 00:19:01,173
-Come here.
-Yes, sir.

318
00:19:03,075 --> 00:19:06,512
<i>The stage manager takes command,</i>

319
00:19:06,845 --> 00:19:11,550
{\an8}<i>and they decide to take down
two of the four scrollers.</i>

320
00:19:13,886 --> 00:19:15,754
<i>Will this resolve the issue?</i>

321
00:19:16,688 --> 00:19:18,624
-Let's test it once.
-Okay.

322
00:19:18,690 --> 00:19:21,226
Sorry, we're going to raise
it one more time.

323
00:19:21,627 --> 00:19:23,295
Okay.

324
00:19:23,362 --> 00:19:26,532
We're going to raise the inner section.

325
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:33,438
It's not working.

326
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:35,574
We took down 100 kilos.

327
00:19:36,408 --> 00:19:38,911
{\an8}That truss is hanging on four lines.

328
00:19:38,977 --> 00:19:40,846
{\an8}Those four lines

329
00:19:41,446 --> 00:19:44,049
{\an8}have a maximum weight capacity
of 800 kilos.

330
00:19:44,116 --> 00:19:46,218
{\an8}That was our calculation.

331
00:19:46,285 --> 00:19:48,754
{\an8}We placed 770 kilos of equipment on it.

332
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:52,724
{\an8}When we tried to pull it up,
it could not raise 770 kilos.

333
00:19:52,891 --> 00:19:54,826
{\an8}MAXIMUM WEIGHT = 800 KILOS
PREPARED EQUIPMENT = 770 KILOS

334
00:19:56,028 --> 00:20:00,165
<i>The scrollers should be within
the specified weight limit,</i>

335
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:01,833
<i>but it still won't rise.</i>

336
00:20:02,768 --> 00:20:04,970
<i>They will have to make some changes.</i>

337
00:20:05,837 --> 00:20:08,640
{\an8}<i>One by one, they remove the scrollers</i>

338
00:20:08,807 --> 00:20:10,943
{\an8}<i>to find out what the problem is.</i>

339
00:20:11,476 --> 00:20:15,180
{\an8}We'll test it again
and call you if we need you.

340
00:20:16,181 --> 00:20:18,050
-What?
-Special effects team!

341
00:20:18,116 --> 00:20:19,985
We're taking them all down?

342
00:20:20,085 --> 00:20:21,920
I'll lift it up.

343
00:20:21,987 --> 00:20:23,455
Okay.

344
00:20:27,259 --> 00:20:30,829
{\an8}<i>They ended up taking down
all four scrollers,</i>

345
00:20:31,263 --> 00:20:33,065
{\an8}<i>but it still won't go up.</i>

346
00:20:34,700 --> 00:20:37,803
<i>All Yabe can do is stand back and wait.</i>

347
00:20:39,938 --> 00:20:41,673
<i>As the investigation continues,</i>

348
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:44,943
<i>the special effects team comes to a halt.</i>

349
00:20:45,844 --> 00:20:47,012
We're sorry!

350
00:20:47,813 --> 00:20:50,582
It feels like I just set up
four concert arenas.

351
00:20:51,683 --> 00:20:55,654
<i>Ueda, the rookie stage facilitator
is frozen in place.</i>

352
00:20:58,123 --> 00:20:59,558
This is life.

353
00:21:03,028 --> 00:21:05,030
<i>It's 10:40 p.m.</i>

354
00:21:06,598 --> 00:21:09,534
<i>Ueda and the stage facilitator team</i>

355
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,870
<i>receive a message from the stage manager.</i>

356
00:21:12,804 --> 00:21:14,873
<i>Attention everyone.</i>

357
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:19,144
<i>As for the center circle,</i>

358
00:21:19,211 --> 00:21:23,348
<i>we got in contact with the truss engineer,</i>

359
00:21:23,415 --> 00:21:25,617
<i>and he will be here around 11:10.</i>

360
00:21:25,684 --> 00:21:28,887
<i>After he gets here,</i>

361
00:21:28,954 --> 00:21:32,324
<i>we can decide what to do.
Personally, I'd like to</i>

362
00:21:32,391 --> 00:21:36,295
<i>revert back to the original plan.</i>

363
00:21:36,361 --> 00:21:38,163
<i>So, whether that's possible</i>

364
00:21:38,463 --> 00:21:41,166
<i>or if it would require extra procedures,</i>

365
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:45,003
<i>is something we'll have to wait until
after 11 to find out.</i>

366
00:21:45,070 --> 00:21:48,106
<i>Then we'll decide if
we'll do it today or tomorrow.</i>

367
00:21:50,008 --> 00:21:50,942
<i>Okay.</i>

368
00:21:54,813 --> 00:21:58,950
<i>The special effects team has to wait for
further notice from the stage manager.</i>

369
00:22:01,553 --> 00:22:04,823
That's the most important thing.

370
00:22:05,524 --> 00:22:09,094
When they have creases,
the air resistance makes them

371
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:10,395
drop slowly.

372
00:22:10,462 --> 00:22:14,299
The dimensions will sparkle
against the lights too.

373
00:22:14,366 --> 00:22:16,735
That's why it's better to crease them.

374
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:19,705
To think that this blows away
in an instant.

375
00:22:20,939 --> 00:22:22,441
Welcome back.

376
00:22:23,508 --> 00:22:27,012
-Tomorrow?
-Tomorrow.

377
00:22:27,612 --> 00:22:33,151
<i>In the end, each team must carry
their work over to the next day.</i>

378
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:36,388
It's the first time experiencing
weight issues.

379
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:39,257
So, these six parts are not done yet.

380
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:46,264
<i>Will the special effects team have to
give up on using the scrollers?</i>

381
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:49,534
<i>It's been a long day.</i>

382
00:22:50,736 --> 00:22:54,439
<i>Signs of fatigue are showing on
the faces of these young workers.</i>

383
00:22:54,906 --> 00:22:57,943
You need to be sharp. You're not sharp.

384
00:22:58,009 --> 00:22:58,844
Okay.

385
00:23:00,011 --> 00:23:02,714
Let's clean up, and we'll go home.

386
00:23:04,015 --> 00:23:06,718
<i>In order to create a special stage,</i>

387
00:23:06,785 --> 00:23:10,822
<i>they must overcome big obstacles.</i>

388
00:23:12,190 --> 00:23:13,925
There were lots of issues.

389
00:23:14,860 --> 00:23:16,428
But I think

390
00:23:17,295 --> 00:23:19,598
tomorrow will be even more difficult.

391
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,503
<i>Time is ticking away.</i>

392
00:23:25,337 --> 00:23:27,806
<i>The countdown to showtime won't stop.</i>

393
00:23:28,874 --> 00:23:32,677
<i>The time left until the first day
of the concert is</i>

